<br>
Whenever I am on, all I get are increasingly constant demands for portage or translocation.  Folks are rarely saying please anymore.  I feel despised.  This is not fun.  I can't even get the darn spell Translocate.  <br>
<br>
Again, as always, Verant confuses (to the extent verant could be said to have thought anything through) frustration/chance with challenge.  Challenge is fun, the other is...NOT.<br>
<br>
End game approaches for me.  The addiction is merely pain.  Is there an EQ Annonymous?</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uammeroutcaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ammer Outcaster</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3/14/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>11:37:58 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Is there an EQ Anonymous?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Well, for the second time yesterday in OT I saw some ooc for a Wizard. Second time I've ever seen that, I had to sigh in awe for a minute and reply to that ooc. I'm a level 39 Wizard with 46 days played and have only seen that twice. LoL, some people are lucky to see it once, other then for ports, translocate, or evacs. To be honest the only thing that keeps me playing my Wizard is the fact that I do not want to start a new character from scratch again. Oh yeah you know what I admired about hitting 39 lastnight? I thought I'd get some nice damage nuke at 39. Ok.. I get Lightning Shock, oh great another magic spellto be resisted. If I remember it's 180 mana opposed to Ice Shock I think it is with 135 mana. Lightning Shock does 381 damage and Ice Shock is 320 damage. So I figured what the hell was the point? You might think after 5 levels from the previous spell level you might see DD's in the 400's for us. Apparently not, I was pretty depressed to see it did only a good 61 more damage. Oh well, what can we do? *sigh*<br>
